In case you missed it, here are the top Sport stories of the week: 1. FORMER SOCCER STAR FOUND DEAD! Former Bidvest Wits midfielder Charles Yohane is no more. Yohane was reportedly murdered during a carjacking in Soweto over the weekend. 2. SHOCK AS PITSO GIVES UP ON HIS COACHING DREAM In an interview with the SA Football Journalist Association (Safja) virtual press conference on Wednesday, Pitso Mosimane (57) revealed that he has given up on his ambitions to coach in Europe. 3. ARROWS COULD BE DOCKED NINE POINTS The Premier Soccer League (PSL) Disciplinary Committee have found Golden Arrows guilty of improper registration of a player. 4. MURDERED EX-SOCCER STAR WAS DRIVING AN UBER! Tributes are pouring in for former soccer star Charles Yohane, whose body was found on Saturday, 12 February. According to reports, the car he used as an Uber driver was hijacked and he was shot. 5. NCIKAZI HAPPY WITH ROYAL TRIP TO ESWATINI Orlando Pirates co-coach, Mandla Ncikazi, has described eSwatini's Royal Leopards qualifying to play in their Caf Confederation Cup group as a "blessing in disguise". 